## Slide 5 — Relevance to Society / Industry

### Why Nutrition Tracking Matters
- **WHO reports** that obesity has tripled worldwide since 1975. Over 1.9 billion adults are overweight.
- In India, **77 million people** are diabetic (IDF 2021), making dietary management critical.
- Accurate, automated food tracking can help prevent chronic diseases and support treatments.

### Real-World Problem Addressed
- Most food recognition apps (MyFitnessPal, Samsung Health) rely on **manual search** or barcode scanning — they cannot recognise food from images reliably, especially Indian food.
- NutriSmart bridges this gap with AI-powered **image-based recognition** that handles both global and Indian cuisines.

### Target Users

| User Segment | Benefit |
|-------------|---------|
| **Fitness Enthusiasts** | Instant calorie tracking from food photos; personalised daily targets |
| **Diabetic Patients** | Monitoring carb/sugar intake; alerts when exceeding limits |
| **Dieticians / Nutritionists** | Tool for client meal analysis; exportable nutrition reports |
| **Hospitals & Clinics** | Standardised patient diet monitoring |
| **General Public** | Easy food-photo-based health awareness |
| **Indian Food Consumers** | Accurate recognition of 30+ Indian dishes not covered by Western apps |

