| 1 | Bossard et al. (Food-101) | 2014 | Random Forest + SURF features | Food-101 (101 classes, 101K images) | 56.4% | Low accuracy; hand-crafted features |
| 2 | Liu et al. (DeepFood) | 2016 | GoogLeNet fine-tuned | Food-101 | 77.4% | Single model, no Indian food |
| 3 | Pandey et al. | 2017 | CNN + Calorie estimation | Food-11 | 83.5% | Only 11 food categories |
| 4 | Mezgec & Seljak | 2017 | InceptionV3 fine-tuned | UNIMIB2016 | 85.0% | European foods only |
| 5 | Jiang et al. (NutritionBot) | 2020 | YOLO + CNN + chatbot | Custom | 81.2% | No RAG; limited food types |
| 6 | MyFitnessPal | 2024 | Manual search / barcode scan | USDA DB | N/A | No image recognition; manual entry only |
| 7 | Google Lens Food Detection | 2024 | Proprietary vision model | Google internal | ~85% | No calorie info; no Indian specialisation |
| 8 | Shivhare & Rani (Indian Food) | 2023 | VGG-16 fine-tuned | Kaggle Indian Food (20 classes) | 87.2% | Small dataset, no ensemble, no chatbot |
| 9 | **NutriSmart (Ours)** | **2026** | **Ensemble MobileNetV2 + Indian Classifier + Gemini Vision + RAG Chatbot** | **Food-101 + Kaggle Indian Food (30 classes)** | **91%+** | **Requires internet for Gemini fallback** |

