```

### Data Flow — Image Classification

```
Food Image (uploaded by user)
    │
    ├─► Saved to /static/temp_upload.jpg
    │
    ▼
YOLOv8 Detection (detect_foods)
    │
    ├─► Bounding boxes + crops for each food item
    │
    ▼ (for each crop)
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Ensemble CNN (3× MobileNetV2)           │
│   Preprocess: resize 224×224, scale [-1,1] │
│   Average softmax → label + confidence  │
│   if confidence ≥ 0.6 → ACCEPT          │
│   else ↓                                │
│                                         │
│ Indian Food Classifier (30 classes)     │
│   if Indian food detected → ACCEPT       │
│   else ↓                                │
│                                         │
│ Gemini Vision API (cloud fallback)      │
│   Sends base64 image → returns label    │
└────────────────┬────────────────────────┘
                 │
                 ▼
Nutrition Lookup (nutrition_service.py)
    │
    ├─► 1. Check local SQLite cache (190+ foods)
    ├─► 2. Fuzzy name matching (underscores ↔ spaces)
    ├─► 3. USDA FoodData Central API fallback
    │
    ▼
Result Page → Show label, calories, protein, carbs, fat, fiber
           → "Log This Meal" button → saves to daily_logs table
```

### RAG Chatbot Flow

```
User Message (e.g., "How many calories in palak paneer?")
    │
    ▼
Sentence Transformer (all-MiniLM-L6-v2)
    │  encodes query → 384-dim vector
    ▼
ChromaDB Semantic Search (L2 distance)
    │  retrieves top-3 matching food descriptions
    │
    ├─► Food NOT in DB? → Gemini fetches nutrition → auto-stores in ChromaDB
    │
    ▼
Gemini LLM (gemini-2.0-flash-lite)
    │  receives: retrieved nutrition data + user profile + query
    │
    ▼
Personalised AI Response
    (cites real nutrition values, considers user's goal/diet/consumed calories)
```

