## Slide 12 — Conclusion

### Key Achievements
- Built **NutriSmart**, a full-stack AI-powered nutrition tracking application.
- Designed and trained a **3-model ensemble (MobileNetV2)** achieving ~91% accuracy on 96 food classes.
- Trained a **dedicated Indian food classifier** on 30 Kaggle classes (~93% accuracy).
- Integrated **YOLOv8** for multi-food plate detection.
- Implemented an **auto-learning RAG chatbot** using ChromaDB, Sentence Transformers, and Gemini — the first open-source nutrition chatbot that permanently expands its knowledge.
- Developed an **ML-based personalised calorie predictor** (Random Forest, R² ≈ 0.97).
- Built a **hybrid nutrition service** with 190+ cached foods and USDA API fallback.

### Problem Solved
NutriSmart eliminates the tedium of manual calorie logging by providing **instant, image-based food recognition** with a special focus on **Indian cuisine**. It empowers users with personalised nutrition tracking, AI-powered guidance, and a self-learning knowledge base — all in a free, open-source package.

### Impact
- Potential to help millions of Indian users manage their diet with technology tailored to their cuisine.
- Demonstrates the viability of ensemble + RAG architectures for domain-specific food recognition applications.
- Fully open-source — can be extended and deployed by students, researchers, and health organisations.

